---
name: playable-banner
description: Create Google Ads playable HTML5 banners for App campaigns. Transforms app screenshots into validated, interactive ad experiences with preview page and downloadable ZIP.
---

# Google Ads Playable Banner Creator

Create playable HTML5 banners for **Google Ads App campaigns** that let users preview and interact with non-gaming apps before installing.

## Workflow

1. **Input** - Receive app screenshots, Figma HTML, brand assets, fonts, and interaction instructions
2. **Analysis** - Understand what part of UI to simulate and how
3. **Development** - Build HTML5 playable using GSAP for smooth animations
4. **Preview** - Deliver preview page with generic phone mockup
5. **Output** - Provide downloadable ZIP ready for Google Ads

---

## Input Expectations

| Asset | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **Screenshots** | Actual app UI screens |
| **Figma HTML** | Exported HTML from Figma designs |
| **Instructions** | WHAT to simulate and HOW |
| **Brand Assets** | App icon, logo, graphics |
| **Fonts** | Google Fonts specifications |

**Creative Direction:** Follow explicit instructions. Propose ideas only when asked.

### Client Asset Request Template

When starting a new playable project, request the following upfront:

| Asset | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **App store listing URL** | Reference for app functionality and existing creative |
| **3-5 high-res screenshots** | Specific screens to recreate (specify which screens needed) |
| **Brand guidelines PDF** | Colors, typography rules, logo usage |
| **Font files or Google Fonts names** | Exact fonts with weights needed |
| **Desired interaction flow description** | What users should do step-by-step |
| **CTA copy preferences** | Preferred button text and headlines |

---

## Output Deliverables

### Preview Page
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                         │
│      ┌───────────────────┐   Screens    │
│      │                   │   ┌────────┐ │
│      │     PLAYABLE      │   │1. Hook │ │ ← Clickable
│      │      PREVIEW      │   │2. Demo │ │   navigation
│      │                   │   │3. CTA  │ │
│      └───────────────────┘   └────────┘ │
│                                         │
│         [ Download ZIP ]                │
│                                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Preview Page Requirements
- **No phone notch overlay** - obscures content during review
- **Clickable screen list** - each screen item navigates directly to that screen
- **PostMessage communication** between preview and iframe:

### ZIP Contents
```
playable-ad.zip
├── index.html    # Main playable with required meta tags
├── styles.css    # Optional (can be inline)
├── script.js     # Optional (can be inline)
└── assets/       # Images, embedded fonts
```

---

## Google Ads Requirements

### File Limits

| Requirement | Specification |
|-------------|---------------|
| Format | `.zip` file |
| Max Size | 5 MB (5.2 MB interstitial) |
| Max Files | 512 files |
| Allowed Types | `.html`, `.css`, `.js`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`, `.svg` |
| File Naming | Letters, numbers, `.`, `-`, `_` only. **NO SPACES** |
| Encoding | UTF-8 |

### Required HTML Structure

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="ad.orientation" content="portrait">
    <meta name="ad.size" content="320x480">
    <script src="https://tpc.googlesyndication.com/pagead/gadgets/html5/api/exitapi.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Content -->
    <button onclick="ExitApi.exit()">Install Now</button>
</body>
</html>
```

### Meta Tags Reference

| Meta Tag | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| `ad.orientation` | **Yes** | Controls display orientation |
| `ad.size` | Optional | Defines base dimensions (e.g., `320x480`). Sometimes needed for proper scaling. |

### Orientation Meta Tags

| Orientation | Meta Tag |
|-------------|----------|
| Portrait (priority) | `<meta name="ad.orientation" content="portrait">` |
| Landscape | `<meta name="ad.orientation" content="landscape">` |
| Both | `<meta name="ad.orientation" content="portrait,landscape">` |

**Always design portrait-first.**

### Allowed External Resources

```html
<!-- Google Fonts -->
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=FontName" rel="stylesheet">

<!-- GSAP (preferred for animations) -->
<script src="https://s0.2mdn.net/ads/studio/cached_libs/tweenmax_1.18.0_499ba64a23378545748ff12d372e59e9_min.js"></script>

<!-- CreateJS -->
<script src="https://s0.2mdn.net/ads/studio/cached_libs/createjs_2015.11.26_54e1c3722102182bb133912ad4442e19_min.js"></script>
```

**All other external URLs are FORBIDDEN.**

### ExitAPI (Critical)

Must be a **literal `<script>` tag in `<head>`** - not loaded dynamically.

```html
<head>
    <script src="https://tpc.googlesyndication.com/pagead/gadgets/html5/api/exitapi.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <button onclick="ExitApi.exit()">Install Now</button>
</body>
```

Without proper ExitAPI, the entire ad becomes clickable (bad UX, accidental clicks).

---

## Asset Optimization

Staying under the 5MB limit requires careful asset management:

| Asset Type | Recommendation |
|------------|----------------|
| **Images** | Use TinyPNG/Squoosh, prefer JPG for photos (80% quality), PNG for UI with transparency |
| **SVGs** | Run through SVGO, remove metadata, editor cruft, and unnecessary attributes |
| **Fonts** | Subset to used characters only (`pyftsubset` or Google Fonts `&text=` parameter) |
| **Code** | Minify JS/CSS before zipping (Terser, cssnano) |

### Image Guidelines

| Format | Use For | Target Size |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| JPG | Photos, gradients, complex imagery | < 100KB each |
| PNG | UI elements, icons with transparency | < 50KB each |
| SVG | Simple icons, logos, shapes | < 5KB each |

### Size Budget Example (5MB total)

```
Images:     ~3.5 MB (70%)
Fonts:      ~500 KB (10%)
HTML/CSS/JS: ~200 KB (4%)
Buffer:     ~800 KB (16%)
```

**Tip:** Limit to 8-10 images maximum. Combine sprites where possible.

---

## Responsive Handling

### Safe Area Strategy

Avoid hardcoded pixel values where possible. Use relative units for scalability:

```css
/* Preferred approach */
.container {
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
    padding: calc(48px + env(safe-area-inset-top)) 16px 16px;
}

.element {
    width: 80%;
    max-width: 320px;
}

/* Font scaling */
.headline {
    font-size: clamp(18px, 5vw, 24px);
}
```

### Sizing Strategy

| Element Type | Recommended Approach |
|--------------|---------------------|
| **Container** | `100vw` × `100vh` |
| **Top padding** | `48px` minimum (clears notches/status bars) |
| **Buttons** | `width: 80%` or `max-width` with percentage |
| **Text** | `clamp()` for responsive sizing |
| **Images** | `object-fit: cover` with percentage-based containers |
| **Touch targets** | Minimum `44px × 44px` |

### Common Viewport Sizes (Portrait)

| Device Class | Width | Test Priority |
|--------------|-------|---------------|
| Small Android | 360px | High |
| iPhone | 390px | High |
| Large phones | 414px | Medium |

### Fixed vs Fluid

```css
/* ❌ Avoid */
.card { width: 300px; left: 30px; }

/* ✅ Prefer */
.card { width: 85%; max-width: 300px; margin: 0 auto; }
```

---

## The 3-Step Engagement Model

```
┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐
│  INTRO/TUTORIAL │ →  │  INTERACTIVE    │ →  │  END CARD/CTA   │
│   (2-3 sec)     │    │  DEMO (10-20s)  │    │   (persistent)  │
└─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘
```

### Step 1: Intro/Tutorial (2-3 seconds)

- **Tutorial hand** showing where to tap/interact
- **Mini-goal**: "Tap to explore", "Swipe to discover"
- **Minimal branding** - save prominent logo for CTA screen
- **No logo clutter** - focus on the hook headline and visual

### Step 2: Interactive Demo (10-20 seconds)

Let users experience the core app feature:

| App Type | Demo Idea |
|----------|-----------|
| E-commerce | Swipe products, add to cart |
| Fitness | Select exercises, see preview |
| Finance | Drag expenses, see savings grow |
| Productivity | Create task, check it off |
| Food Delivery | Browse menu, customize order |
| Travel | Explore destinations, swipe photos |

**Interaction patterns:** Tap, Swipe, Drag & Drop, Hold, Scroll

### Step 3: End Card/CTA (Persistent)

- **Prominent branding**: Large centered logo (bigger than other screens)
- **Headline**: Centered, reinforcing value proposition
- **Visual content**: Product grid, feature showcase, or celebration
- **Primary CTA button**: "Install Free", "Get the App", "Continue in App"
- **Store badge**: Google Play / App Store logo at bottom
- Optional replay button

#### CTA Screen Layout Structure
```
┌─────────────────────────┐
│                         │
│      [ BIG LOGO ]       │  ← Centered, prominent
│                         │
│    Compelling Headline  │  ← Centered
│                         │
│   ┌─────┬─────┬─────┐   │
│   │     │     │     │   │  ← Visual content
│   │     │     │     │   │    (sized appropriately,
│   │     │     │     │   │     not too large)
│   └─────┴─────┴─────┘   │
│                         │
│  [ Continue in App ]    │  ← Primary CTA
│                         │
│     ▶ Google Play       │  ← Store badge at bottom
│                         │
└─────────────────────────┘
```

### CTA Placement

**Portrait:** Bottom 15-20% of screen
**Landscape:** Right 20-25% of screen

CTA should be **always visible** with progressive prominence (subtle → prominent).

### Layout Considerations for Phone Displays

| Element | Guideline |
|---------|-----------|
| **Top padding** | Use 48px+ to clear phone notches and status bars |
| **Logo on intermediate screens** | Remove or minimize - save prominence for CTA |
| **Logo on CTA screen** | Centered, larger than anywhere else |
| **Visual content (grids, images)** | Size conservatively - leave breathing room |
| **Clickable areas** | Ensure any click on demo screens progresses the flow |

---

## Technical Constraints

- Must work in sandboxed iframe (`allow-scripts` only)
- No `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`
- No `<iframe>`, `<frame>`, or `<frameset>` tags
- Explicit end tags required: `<path></path>` not `<path />`
- Images for canvas: use `crossorigin="anonymous"`
- Sound: **never auto-play** - only after user interaction

---

## Pre-Flight Checklist

Run through this checklist before every submission:

### File Structure
- [ ] ZIP file under 5MB (5.2MB for interstitial)
- [ ] No spaces in any filenames
- [ ] Only allowed file types (`.html`, `.css`, `.js`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`, `.svg`)
- [ ] All filenames use only `a-z`, `0-9`, `.`, `-`, `_`
- [ ] UTF-8 encoding on all files

### Required Code
- [ ] `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration present
- [ ] `<meta name="ad.orientation" content="portrait">` in `<head>`
- [ ] ExitAPI script as **literal `<script>` tag in `<head>`** (not dynamically loaded)
- [ ] CTA button calls `ExitApi.exit()`

### External Resources
- [ ] All external URLs are Google-approved (fonts.googleapis.com, s0.2mdn.net)
- [ ] No unauthorized third-party scripts or resources
- [ ] No `<iframe>`, `<frame>`, or `<frameset>` tags

### UX & Accessibility
- [ ] Touch targets are ≥ 44px × 44px
- [ ] Top padding ≥ 48px (clears notches/status bars)
- [ ] Tutorial hand/guidance on first interaction
- [ ] CTA always visible and functional

### Testing
- [ ] Validated at **https://h5validator.appspot.com/adwords/asset** (select "App Campaigns")
- [ ] Validator confirms ExitAPI is detected
- [ ] Tested on multiple viewport sizes (360px, 390px, 414px width)
- [ ] All interactions work on touch devices

---

## Common Rejection Fixes

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| Invalid fourth party call | External URL | Remove non-Google URLs |
| Unacceptable HTML5 ad | Missing tags | Add DOCTYPE, orientation meta |
| File size too large | ZIP > 5MB | Compress images, minify code |
| Dimensions not allowed | Wrong meta | Use `ad.orientation` instead |
| Unsupported file type | Bad file in ZIP | Remove `.mp4`, `.mp3`, etc. |
| High CTR low CVR | ExitAPI wrong | Move to literal `<script>` in `<head>` |
| Characters not supported | Spaces in names | Use only `a-z`, `0-9`, `.`, `-`, `_` |

---

## Validation

Test at: **https://h5validator.appspot.com/adwords/asset**

- Select "App Campaigns" checkbox
- Upload the ZIP file
- Verify CTA shows ExitAPI confirmation

---

## Best Practices

### Do

- Prioritize portrait, then landscape
- Show tutorial hand on first interaction
- One core feature demo only
- Immediate feedback for every interaction
- CTA always visible, increasing prominence
- Use GSAP for smooth animations
- Save prominent branding for CTA screen
- Add sufficient top padding (48px+) to clear phone UI
- Make clickable screen navigation in preview page
- Use relative units (`%`, `vw`, `vh`, `clamp()`) for scalability
- Compress all images before adding to ZIP
- Test at h5validator before delivery

### Don't

- Auto-play sound
- Overwhelm with features
- Hide CTA completely
- Use non-Google external resources
- Use localStorage/sessionStorage
- Use iframes
- Forget tutorial guidance
- Clutter intermediate screens with logos
- Cut off images with improper aspect ratios (use `object-fit: cover`)
- Make visual grids too large - leave breathing room
- Use hardcoded pixel values for layout
- Skip validation testing
